      "avatarPath" : "./download/file.php%3Favatar=33850_1330660399.jpg"
    },
    "content" : "You should most definitely do the trip. I have purchased several early '60's Beetles from Sweden and drove them all home. Waiting on one as I type now, the road trips are the best part of classic VW ownership. Just be sensible and prepared, pack some tools, spares, maps/sat nav and clean pants. Is is roughly 1300-1400 miles from Sweden back to the UK, 7 countries in around 3 or 4 days and that is with an unknown vehicle! You at least have somewhere to sleep, eat &amp; rest on your trip.\n<br> Go for it and put yourself outside your comfort zone. Expect the worst but hope for the best...you will not regret it.\n<br> Take a camera and record your adventure.\n<br> \n<br> All the best,\n<br> \n<br> Johnny",
    "lastEdited" : "Mon May 14, 2012 6:22 pm"
